data-triple-N3.o: "Canterbury is an historic English cathedral city, which lies at the heart of the City of Canterbury, a district of Kent in South East England. It lies on the River Stour. Originally a Brythonic settlement called *Durouernon (composed of the ancient British roots *duro- "stronghold", *uerno- "alder tree"), it was renamed Durovernum Cantiacorum by the Roman conquerors in the 1st century AD."@en
